edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.datastructures.textannotation

Class Constituent

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.datastructures.textannotation.Constituent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Constituent
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A Constituent represents a unit of text (not necessarily contiguous) that participates in a view. In terms of the nodes and edges representation of views, Constituents are the nodes and Relations are edges. Each Constituent corresponds to a set of tokens in a TextAnnotation.
    Author:
    Vivek Srikumar
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • Constituent

        public Constituent(String label,
                   String viewName,
                   TextAnnotation text,
                   int start,
                   int end)
        start, end offsets are token indexes, and use one-past-the-end indexing -- so a one-token constituent right at the beginning of a text has start/end (0,1) offsets are relative to the entire text span (i.e. NOT sentence-relative) This constructor assigns default score to constituent
        Parameters:
        label - label of this Constituent
        viewName - name of View this Constituent belongs to
        text - TextAnnotation this Constituent belongs to
        start - start token offset
        end - end token offset (one-past-the-end)

      • Constituent

        public Constituent(String label,
                   double score,
                   String viewName,
                   TextAnnotation text,
                   int start,
                   int end)
        start, end offsets are token indexes, and use one-past-the-end indexing -- so a one-token constituent right at the beginning of a text has start/end (0,1) offsets are relative to the entire text span (i.e. NOT sentence-relative)
        Parameters:
        label - label of this Constituent
        score - confidence in label
        viewName - name of View this Constituent belongs to
        text - TextAnnotation this Constituent belongs to
        start - start token offset
        end - end token offset (one-past-the-end)

        public String getTokenizedSurfaceForm()
        This method returns a tokenized representation of the surface form of the constituent. This is not the original surface form of the constituent. To retrieve that, please use getSurfaceForm()
        Returns:
        A constructed form based on the tokens covered by the constituent and a single whitespace separating them.
